Validates and sorts the task backlog by impact (highâ†’low) and difficulty (easyâ†’hard), maintaining two fixed enums and three public entry points for normalization and display ordering.

The backlog is stored as a bare `Vec<Row>` in insertion order; `priority_sorted` returns a cloned, reordered copy without mutating the store. The impact and difficulty vocabularies are hardcoded as 3-element arrays (`["high", "medium", "low"]` and `["easy", "medium", "hard"]`); any task file using different values will fail validation.

`normalize_impact(impact: &str) -> Result<String, StatusError>` and `normalize_difficulty(difficulty: &str) -> Result<String, StatusError>` accept case-insensitive input, return the canonical lowercase spelling, or error with `BadImpact`/`BadDifficulty`. The helper `rank(value: &str, known: &[&str; 3]) -> usize` returns the 0-based index of a value in a known array, or `known.len()` for anything else â€” this ensures sorting never panics on unexpected store state (hand-edited files) but is guaranteed never hit after normalization has run.

`priority_sorted(store: &Store) -> Vec<Row>` sorts by impact rank first, then difficulty rank within ties; the sort is stable, so ties keep insertion order.